<title>UK: Navia and E+H have 93 pct of Whessoe.</title>
<headline>Navia and E+H have 93 pct of Whessoe.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Norway's Navia ASA and its Swiss partner, Endress + Hauser Finanz AG said on Tuesday they had roughly 93.0 percent of Whessoe Plc under their joint bid for the British instrument controls group.</p>
<p>The joint bid valued Whessoe at about 53 million stg.</p>
<p>By Thursday afternoon, the companies had received valid acceptances for 12.9 million shares, or about 42.4 percent of Whessoe's ordinary share capital.</p>
<p>This was in addition to the 50.6 percent stake Navia and Endress bought in their bid, the companies said in a statement.</p>
<p>The offer will remain open for acceptances until April 10.</p>
